cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with unsupervised image-to-image translation using GANs, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method incorporates instance information and improves multi-instance transfiguration, which involves learning the identity function outside of target instances, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a sequential mini-batch inference/training technique, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
